<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Derenath:
[B]I'd suggest you solo elsewhere. The drakes' aggro range and AE nuke/strip is a death warrant for any class that can't invis themselves. And believe me you will run into drakes.

There's no safe zone close enough to run to if things get bad. Druids and wizards quad kite around there and the less skillful may drop one or 4 wyverns on yer head. The mobs aren't undead and have quite a few hp's for thier level so you'll be medding ALOT. I'd say you're making things unecessisarily difficult for your self. Any positive giant faction you gain wouldn't be worth the effort.

If you're dead set on it though, bind at the zone wall farthest to the right as you face the water near the shore. Any faction hit you take would be -dragon and +storm giant.

If you solo occasionally, go to Karnor's Castle or hit the undeads around Dreadlands. There's enough undead there to make soloing as a cleric worth the time until 54-55, enchanters you can buy clarity from, much safer places to bind, and safer zones to run to. Also, the live critters have fewer hp's, don't hit as hard, and don't AE frost/strip.

I LOATHE Cobalt Scar.
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
